FilterData API

API for normalization and quality scoring of contact data before loading it into CRM systems. 

FilterData normalizes phone numbers, emails and personal names and helps detect problematic records before they enter CRM, marketing systems or lead databases.

Typical use cases

cleaning leads before importing into CRM

phone number normalization

email standardization

duplicate reduction

improving contact database quality

What the API does

FilterData accepts contact data and returns:

normalized values

technical data quality score (QC)

human-readable explanation of the result

Supported fields
phone
name
email
Example request

POST

https://filterdata.ru/demo/api/v1/demo/normalize

Body

{
  "phone": "8 (999) 123-45-67",
  "name": "иван иванов",
  "email": "EXAMPLE@mail.com"
}
Example response
{
  "phone": "+79991234567",
  "name": "Иванов Иван",
  "email": "ivanov@example.com",
  "qc": 0,
  "explanation": "Data is valid and ready for use."
}
Data Quality Levels (QC)

QC indicates the technical quality of the record.

QC	Level	Description
0	VALID	Data is correct
1	ACCEPTABLE	Acceptable but not perfect
2	RISK	Suspicious data
3	PARTIAL	Incomplete data
4	MISSING	Field is missing
Example of risky data
Иванов Ivan

Mixed Cyrillic and Latin characters.

